    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing five species of gregarious, colony-forming rodents that live in extensive burrow systems in grasslands of plains, high plateaus, and montain valleys in North America, and have a call resembling a dog's bark.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
